<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="71">
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, DR" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington" pageId="29" pageNumber="84" pagination="273 - 278" title="Two new fern-feeding sawflies of the genus Aneugmenus Hartig (Hymenoptera: Tenthredinidae) from South America." volume="107" year="2005">Smith (2005)</bibRefCitation>
recorded two species in northern South America, Venezuela, Colombia, and Ecuador, the southern extent of this Holarctic genus. One species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hartig, 1837" authorityName="Hartig" authorityYear="1837" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Aneugmenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aneugmenus merida" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="merida">Aneugmenus merida</taxonomicName>
Smith, was reared from bracken fern, 
<taxonomicName class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dennstaedtiaceae" genus="Pteridium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pteridium aquilinum" order="Polypodiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aquilinum">Pteridium aquilinum</taxonomicName>
(L.) in Venezuela. The specimen collected here is a male and could be either of the two species; the male is not known for 
<taxonomicName authority="Hartig, 1837" authorityName="Hartig" authorityYear="1837" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Aneugmenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aneugmenus colombia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colombia">Aneugmenus colombia</taxonomicName>
Smith.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
